Flamboyant businessman Steve Mbogo has started 2017 with a lot of excitement following the birth of his daughter.Mbogo, who has declared interest in the Starehe Parliamentary seat, took to social media on Sunday to share the good news with his fans.He revealed that his wife had just been put to bed before adding that they had picked the name Meysam for their little bundle of joy.The self-proclaimed billionaire could not hide his elation saying God should "protect, provide and brighten her life."The newborn is Mbogo's second child with Sabrina, who is the sister to KTN's Maisha Mzuqa host Jamal Gaddafi. Congratulations are in order!